  "evidence_entities": [
    {
      "id": "paper_id:abstract:1:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "paper_id",
      "text_span_id": "abstract_1",
      "text": "Of all congenital adrenal hyperplasia (CAH), 95% to 99% is 21-hydroxylase deficiency (21OHD), an autosomal recessive disease.",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "paper_id:abstract:2:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "paper_id",
      "text_span_id": "abstract_2",
      "text": "21OHD is due to an insufficiency of 21-hydroxylase enzyme, which is encoded by the CYP21A2 gene and involved in cortisol and aldosterone production.",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "paper_id:introduction:1:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "paper_id",
      "text_span_id": "introduction_1",
      "text": "Through a negative feedback system, the lack of cortisol synthesis causes an increase in adrenocorticotropic hormone (ACTH) that determines hyperplasia of the adrenal cortex due to the continuous overstimulation and hypersecretion of precursors upstream of the enzyme defect.",
      "confidence": 0.9,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "paper_id:introduction:2:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "paper_id",
      "text_span_id": "introduction_2",
      "text": "The 21OH enzyme converts 17\u03b1-hydroxyprogesterone to 11-deoxycortisol and progesterone to deoxycorticosterone.",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "paper_id:introduction:3:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "paper_id",
      "text_span_id": "introduction_3",
      "text": "Classic 21OHD is further divided into salt-wasting (SW) (cortisol and aldosterone deficiency) and simple virilizing (SV) phenotype (cortisol and milder aldosterone deficiency).",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "paper_id:genetics:1:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "paper_id",
      "text_span_id": "genetics_1",
      "text": "CYP21A2 (OMIM*613815), encoding the steroid 21OH enzyme, and CYP21A1P pseudogene involve 10 exons spanning 3.4 kb. These genes share 98% sequence homology in exons and around 96% sequence homology in introns.",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "paper_id:genetics:2:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "paper_id",
      "text_span_id": "genetics_2",
      "text": "Over 95% of deleterious variants leading to 21OHD are attributable to intergenic recombination events where microconversions, consisting in the transfer to CYP21A2 of deleterious variants usually present in the CYP21A1P pseudogene, represent 70% to 75%.",
      "confidence": 0.9,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "paper_id:genetics:3:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "paper_id",
      "text_span_id": "genetics_3",
      "text": "The genetic cause of CAH-X syndrome is a recombination event between TNXB and its pseudogene TNXA. The resulting 30 kb deletion includes the entire CYP21A2 gene sequence and part of the TNXB gene and produces a chimeric TNXA/TNXB gene.",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "paper_id:genetics:4:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "paper_id",
      "text_span_id": "genetics_4",
      "text": "The functional consequence of this rearrangement is the complete absence of the 21OH enzyme and the deficiency of tenascin-X, while the resulting phenotype is a hypermobility form of Ehlers-Danlos syndrome (EDS).",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    }
  ],
